  "body": "### Description\n\nCurrent methods for installing the Quarkus CLI require an additional package manager like SDKMAN!, Jbang, etc...\r\n\r\nWhen building a container for developer use, it would be nice to have a mechanism to install the Quarkus CLI without having to install a package manager.  The package managers like SDKMAN!, or JBang, also install locally to the user running the command which can make it difficult with images which run as arbitrary users.\n\n### Implementation ideas\n\nIdeas:\r\n\r\n1. Provide an RPM install\r\n1. Provide a shell script which installs to a specified path, aka `/usr/local/bin`",
